        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17910",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "First to solve the detection problems before handling the undetectable \"C\" locale.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-14T02:47:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-14T02:47:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17959",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=weppos",
                        "name": "weppos",
                        "displayName": "Simone Carletti",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I just come across this issue.\nI work on a MacBook Pro and I created a simple Zend_Service_Delicious script.\n\nThis issue causes Zend_Service_Delicious to fail when called via shell on my Mac.\nI posted all details here ZF-2318.\n\nAbout this issue I [http:\/\/www.icynorth.com\/forums\/viewtopic.php?p=1917&sid=ea9e75a6518fbc41f62e21beea5523ff|found a topic] that apparently describes the same problem.\nI vote +1 for a default locale setting on detection failure.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=weppos",
                        "name": "weppos",
                        "displayName": "Simone Carletti",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-16T07:11:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-16T07:11:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17961",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry, but Zend_Service_Delicious has NOTHING to do with Zend_Locale.\nYou can solve your problem this way:\n\n{code}\nsetlocale(LC_ALL, 'it_IT');\n$service = new Zend_Service_Delicious();\n{code}\n\nIn general the problem is that Zend_Service_Delicious does not handle exceptions from Zend_Locale properly.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-16T10:59:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-16T10:59:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17962",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=weppos",
                        "name": "weppos",
                        "displayName": "Simone Carletti",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Thomas, \n\nI know that the _specific_ Zend_Service_Delicious issue has nothing to do with this Zend_Locale issue.\nThis is why I posted ZF-2318 under the proper Zend_Service_Delicious category.\n\nHowever, my comment was to point out how executing Zend_Locale under Mac Osx via shell causes \n\n{code}\nsetlocale(LC_ALL, 0);\n{code}\n\nto return *C* string instead of a valid locale variable and, in general, it causes Zend_Locale to throw an Exception.\nIn this specific issue, my comment was a kind of agreement to your 'default locale' suggestion. :)\n\nI also noticed that Zend_Locale autodetection calls this function\n\n{code}\n    \/**\n     * Returns the locale which the framework is set to\n     *\/\n    public function getFramework()\n    {\n        $languages = array();\n        return $languages;\n    }\n{code} \n\nbut it seems closed to itself without any possibility of adding defaul languages without extending the class itself.\nIs it a bug or a design decision? (May be this should be a different issue?)\n\nPS. About Zend_Service_Delicious, I already used setlocale(LC_ALL, 'en_US'); as a workaround before and it works but I think something should be improved in the class itself, this is why I opened a new issue at ZF-2318.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=weppos",
                        "name": "weppos",
                        "displayName": "Simone Carletti",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-16T11:17:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-16T11:17:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17963",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The getFramework() method was added because when this proposal was made there was a discussion of adding a generic framework wide config.\n\nThere is still a proposal which aims to do so... this is what this method was made for.\nAs the related proposal is still not implemented the method is still empty.\n\nThis is no bug, it was a design decision of the dev-team.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-16T13:45:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-16T13:45:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17964",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=weppos",
                        "name": "weppos",
                        "displayName": "Simone Carletti",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}As the related proposal is still not implemented the method is still empty.{quote}\n\nThanks for your clarifications, Thomas.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=weppos",
                        "name": "weppos",
                        "displayName": "Simone Carletti",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-16T14:48:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-16T14:48:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17981",
